<strong>Output:</strong> A sheet of paper, covered in black. Upon retrieval with the robotic arm, the piece of paper immediately burst in flames. Fire lasted for only a couple seconds. Inspection of the scorch marks on the robotic arm indicates that a human hand would suffer second-degree burns, up to third if it lasted longer.</p>
<p><em>Note: Writing the apology note with a pencil was a HUGE mistake, seems 914 changed the graphite from the writing into very fine coal powder, and because of [REDACTED] set itself ablaze right upon contact&#8230; Also, sentient or not, I think this machine may dislike me now, I think it would be best for me to stay away from it for some time. - RE Pewny</em></p>
